HEADWORD: Sacerdotalism
<hw>Sac`er*do"tal*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The system,
style, spirit, or character, of a priesthood, or sacerdotal order;
devotion to the interests of the sacerdotal order.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

